==English==
{{wikipedia}}
[[Image:EU_location_EST.png|thumb|200 px|Location of Estonia]]

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|Esthonia}} (dated)

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|Estonia|lang=la}}, whence also Russian {{term|Эстония|lang=ru}}. Other early Latin forms were {{term|Estia|lang=la}} and {{term|Hestia|lang=la}}, possibly derived from the tribal name {{term|Aesti|lang=la}} described by the [[Roman]] historian [[w:Tacitus|Tacitus]] in his Germania (ca. 98 AD). Compare also {{langname|non}} {{term|Eistland||Estonia|lang=is}}, {{langname|de}} {{term|Estland||Estonia|lang=de}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ɛsˈtəʊ.ni.ə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɛsˈtoʊ.ni.ə/}}
* {{audio|en-us-Estonia.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|əʊniə}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A country in North East Europe. Official name: [[Republic of Estonia]].

